events.name: New York Knicks at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Alec Burks hit a 3-pointer for New York's final points and finished off Detroit with a last-second steal in the Knicks' 104-102 victory over the Pistons on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alec Burks, R.J. Barrett lead Knicks past Pistons, 104-102

headlines.description: — Celtics coach Ime Udoka has his priorities set for the final push to the playoffs, and trying to figure out Boston's best matchup isn't among them.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics beat T'Wolves 134-112, take over top spot in East

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Corey Kispert scored 16 of his career-high 25 points in the first half, and the Washington Wizards beat the struggling Golden State Warriors 123-115 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards hand Warriors 5th loss in 6 games, 123-115

headlines.description: — Jae Crowder's wide-open 3-pointer late in the fourth quarter Sunday sealed yet another win for the Phoenix Suns, who continue to pile up victories even though they've accomplished just about everything possible in an NBA regular season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker has 35 points, Suns beat 76ers for 8th win in a row

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram's strained hamstring healed in time for him to return from a 10-game absence against the team that drafted him — and in a matchup holding postseason implications for both clubs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram scores 26 in return, Pelicans top Lakers 116-108

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving waited all season for a chance to play in front of his home fans, and this sure wasn't the way he envisioned it going.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball scores 33 points, Hornets spoil Irving's home debut

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic knows the Mavericks haven't had home-court advantage in the playoffs since the young superstar came to Dallas.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavs top Jazz 114-100 for inside track to home court
